EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 282300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING AND MONDAY A DISRUPTING TROUGH WILL RUN SEWARDS FM THE
ATLANTIC ACROSS THE UK AND INTO EUROPE AND THEN SLWY FILL. AN AREA OF HIGH
PRESSURE 1030 WILL LIE NEAR THE BALTIC. THE AZORES HIGH WILL EXTEND A WEAK
RIDGE TO THE W OF THE UK AND THEN CONNECT WITH THE BALTIC HIGH ON TUESDAY
AS PRESSURE BUILDS ACROSS THE UK.
A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 972 WILL LIE IN MID ATLANTIC.
A SIMILAR PRESSURE PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH WEDNESDAY WITH THE BALTIC
HIGH PRESSURE DOMINANT ACROSS THE UK. ON SUNDAY EVENING AND MONDAY WINDS
WILL BE STRG AT TIMES IN ALL SEA AREAS LIKELY SE IN THE N SEA AND SW IN
DOVER AND WIGHT. WINDS WILL TEND TO MOD LATER IN THE S. ON TUESDAY WINDS
WILL BE OCNL STRG AT FIRST IN THE N. OCNL STRG NE WINDS MAY DEVELOP ON WEDNESDAY
